## Critical Finding: Orphaned Gitlinks

The parent Income.git treats both nested repos as **mode 160000 gitlinks** (the internal representation git uses for submodules) — but **without a `.gitmodules` file**. This is a half-submodule state that git arrived at because the nested repos were committed while inside the working tree.

```
# git ls-files --stage in parent shows:
160000 4aa4798c...  0  Flows/LOBs/Income-Land-Deal-Search   ← gitlink, recorded at codebase-merge commit
160000 99fbd57b...  0  Flows/LOBs/wholesaling               ← gitlink, recorded at codebase-merge commit
```

**What this means:**
- `git status` shows both as `M` (modified) because their current HEADs differ from what parent recorded
- Anyone who clones `Income.git` gets **empty directories** at these paths (gitlink with no .gitmodules = unresolvable)
- `git submodule update --init` will fail — nothing to initialize without .gitmodules
- The parent has never committed the new gitlink positions; the recorded hashes point to the codebase-merge commits, not the current wave-5 state

**Root-level deleted gitlinks** (also present in parent index, staged as deleted — never cleaned up):
```
160000 852dbb1...  0  Income-Land-Deal-Search   ← pre-Flows/LOBs/ location (D in working tree)
160000 017c4a7...  0  wholesaling               ← pre-Flows/LOBs/ location (D in working tree)
160000 bcaa552...  0  blender3D-poc             ← also gone; dirs don't exist (D in working tree)
160000 ee55216...  0  fleecebookmarketpacer     ← also gone; dirs don't exist (D in working tree)
```
These four root-level gitlink entries exist in the parent index as "deleted" but have never been removed in a commit. They are part of the parent's massive uncommitted state.

